Rating: 3
A very good recipe. It is simple and lets the flavor of the salmon shine. I used low-sodium soy sauce and sprinkled some sea salt before serving. I only made the sauce and then grilled the fresh wild Pacific salmon with my Le Creuset grill. It was delicious. I served it with sauteed spinach, julienned Japanese cucumbers, and Japanese rice. It was quick, and will make this often.

Rating: 3
Great flavor! I cheated because I had a bottle of Japanese Ponzu sauce in my pantry. I red pepper flakes to make sure it had a little zing. I am going to save this Ponzu sauce recipe so I don't have to drive 20 miles when I run out of the bottled sauce. I also made the Vegetable Slaw which was worth the effort and a good accompaniment to the salmon.

Rating: 3
The recipe verbatum is excellent. It's taste is a little lost on the salmon once the slaw is put on. My husband seared the salmon and it was incredibly most. The sauce could be used for dipping - it is a well balanced hot/sweet blend.